Apr 21 2009 	Everything you like about France in the Heart of San Francisco	If you like France - and I mean all of France, not just Paris - you will love Cornell Hotel de France in San Francisco. It's the real deal, run by a wonderful French Family who came to San Francisco back in the 60's and over time turned this 1908 6-story Victorian into an authentic French country style hotel and restaurant. In part dedicated to the patron saint of Orleans, Joan of Arc, in part dedicated to French Impressionism, the hotel is decorated with such individual touch and thoughtfulness that you will really feel the wings of time and place when you're there. It will add another exquisite cultural level to what already is a great cultural experience - San Francisco - and they won't charge you an arm and a leg for it. The hotel has all the necessary amenities, a full breakfast is included, and, of course, you have to try the restaurant for dinner, as well! My wife and I and our daughter never stay any place else when we visit San Francisco!!!	
Apr 19 2009 	Taste of France in San Francisco	A stay at the Cornell Hotel is a tiptoe into another country and another time. I love the feeling of contrast when I step out the front door, back to the hubbub of Bush Street and the cable car turnaround at the base of Powell. Tucked inside the Cornell are its welcoming proprietors, Madame and Monsieur Lambert; an elevator that hearkens back to an earlier century; floors that pay homage to Matisse, Modigliani, and more; and a taste of France, awaiting visitors and locals alike, in the Jeanne d'Arc Restaurant below. For twenty-five years, my father stayed at the Cornell Hotel, befriending its owners and making it his second home in San Francisco. I love that I can return there in my father's stead and be welcomed as family, feeling his presence on every floor.	
